LEONARD against FULKERSON. ON CERTIORARI. At the trial below, on the return of the jury, the justice entered the verdict in his docket in figures, and not in words at length; but rendered no judgment. Halsted

moved the reversal of the proceedings below; first, that there was not any judgment rendered. But if the entry of the verdict by the justice could be substituted for -a judgment, yet it was in figures, and not in words at length.

By the Court.

There is no judgment. Let the proceedings below be rendered void.

Proceedings made void.
